002100240320:help Name='DISPLAY'.Account Type Code Maintenace - Help
002200240320:p.This screen allows for the maintanence of the financial class account type
002300240320data. Enter a number in the option column in front of the account type code you
002400240320want to do maintenance on. You must have authority to add, change or delete an
002500240320account type code or its corresponding data; otherwise, you will only be able
002600240320to view the data. Place the cursor on the search line and press F1 (HELP) to
002700240320learn how to search for the account type code you are after.
002800240320:p.
002900240320:p.The following function keys are available:
003000240320:ul.
003100240320:li.:hp2.F1:ehp2. - Help text for the various fields on the screen.
003200240320:li.:hp2.F3:ehp2. - Exit out of the program.
003300240320:li.:hp2.F5:ehp2. - Refresh the screen to the way it first appeared.
003400240320:li.:hp2.F6:ehp2. - Add a pay code change to account type code entry.
003500240320:li.:hp2.F11:ehp2. - Switch between searching by type and descritpion.
003600240320:li.:hp2.F12:ehp2. - Cancel all processing and go back to previous screen.
003700240320:li.:hp2.F14:ehp2. - Switch between showing all accounts and only active
003800240320accounts.
003900240320:li.:hp2.F16:ehp2. - Initial billing days after the DOS Maintenance
004000240320:li.:hp2.F24:ehp2. - Rotate through displaying the different function keys.
004100240320:eul.
004200240320:ehelp.
004300240320.*
004400240320.*******************************************************************************
004500240320:help Name='SRCH4TEXT'.Search For - Help
004600240320:p.Searching is done on the either the code or description column. The column
004700240320header of the active search column will appear in a different color than the
004800240320rest of the columns. Also, the search text description will have the name of the
004900240320column being searched on. If the current search column is the account type code,
005000240320then entering a value into the search field will cause the program to position
005100240320to or search on the account type code. If the current search column is the
005200240320account type code description, then the program will postion to or search on
005300240320the account type code description.
005400240320:p.
005500240320:p.There are two types of searching you can do:
005600240320:ul.
005700240320:li.:hp2.Positon:ehp2. - You can enter just a portion of the value you want to
005800240320position to. For Example, if you are searching for an account type code that
005900240320starts with H, then you can enter an H in the search field and press ENTER. The
006000240320first row of subfile data will have the account type that starts with H, or the
006100240320next closest letter if there is not account type that starts with H.
006200240320:li.:hp2.Search:ehp2. - By placing a question mark (?) at the beginning of the
006300240320search text, you can search within the account type code or account type code
006400240320description for matching values.  You can enter just a portion of the of the
006500240320value you want to search for.  For Example, if you know what you want a account
006600240320type code description that has MEDICAID in it, you can enter ?MEDICAID in the
006700240320search line and press ENTER. On the screen will appear all account type code
006800240320descriptions that have MEDICAID in them.
006900240320:eul.
007000240320:ehelp.
