007200240320.*******************************************************************************
007300240320:help Name='OPTION'.Option Number - Help
007400240416:p.Enter one of the below numbers into into the option column before the
007500240416account type code you would like to display, modify or delete.
007600240320:p.
007700240320:ul.
007800240320:li.:hp2.2:ehp2. = Change the data for the account type code. You must have
007900240320authority to do this.
008000240320:li.:hp2.4:ehp2. = Delete the account type code and any associated account type
008100240320code data. You must have authority to do this.
008200240320:li.:hp2.5:ehp2. = View the data for the account type code.
008300240320:eul.
008400240320:ehelp.
008500240320.*
008600240320.*******************************************************************************
008700240320:help Name='ATMATYPE'.Account Type Code - Help
008800240320:p.Is the two character code associated with the Financial Class Account Type.
008900240320For example, :hp2.CIGNA MCARE DME:ehp2. is assigned the code value of
009000240320:hp2.CM:ehp2..
009100240320:ehelp.
009200240320.*
009300240320.*******************************************************************************
009400240320:help Name='ATMADESC'.Account Type Code Description - Help
009500240320:p.The description of what the Account Type Code is.  This is usually the full
009600240320name of the business that the code is assigned to. For example, the account type
009700240320code :hp2.X:ehp2. has the description of :hp2.MEDICARE/MEDICAID:ehp2..
009800240320
009900240320:ehelp.
010000240320.*
010100240320.*******************************************************************************
010200240320:help Name='ATMINACDT'.Inactive Date - Help
010300240320:p.The inactive date is the date that the code was marked as no longer being
010400240320used. You can hide pay codes change to account type codes from the screen by
010500240320pressing the F14 key.
010600240320:ehelp.
